The paper proposes a Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) architecture for autonomous driving, specifically for on-ramp merging. This involves modeling an interactive environment and optimizing long-term objectives while safely executing near-term actions. The paper applies a Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) architecture and a Deep Q-Network (DQN) to approximate the Q-function for action selection. This work involves machine learning, robotics, and computer vision, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV, and cs.SY.
